<subSubSection pageId="39" pageNumber="38" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="39.[192,1440,1254,1314]" pageId="39" pageNumber="38">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,316,1254,1280]" pageId="39" pageNumber="38">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The midelytral black fascia traverses the sutural margin in specimens of this species, which is not the case in superficially similar specimens of 
<taxonomicName box="[652,757,1288,1314]" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Axina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="39" pageNumber="38" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="basalis">
<emphasis box="[652,671,1288,1314]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="38">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[683,757,1288,1314]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="38">basalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="39" pageNumber="38" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="39.[192,1440,1329,1625]" pageId="39" pageNumber="38">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,356,1329,1355]" pageId="39" pageNumber="38">Redescription</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[371,414,1330,1356]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="38">Size</emphasis>
. Length 14.0 mm; width 
<quantity box="[709,801,1330,1356]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.3" pageId="39" pageNumber="38" unit="mm" value="3.3">3.3 mm</quantity>
. 
<emphasis box="[813,872,1330,1355]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="38">Form</emphasis>
. As in 
<figureCitation box="[958,1052,1329,1356]" captionStart="Figures 118–121" captionStartId="70.[192,279,1859,1885]" captionTargetBox="[192,1440,213,1828]" captionTargetId="figure-40@70.[192,1440,213,1828]" captionTargetPageId="70" captionText="Figures 118–121. Habitus of Axina species. 118) Axina trinalis. 119) A. acutipennis. 120) A. fortipes. 121) A. furcula." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4565041" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4565041/files/figure.png" pageId="39" pageNumber="38">Fig. 120</figureCitation>
. 
<emphasis box="[1065,1126,1329,1355]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="38">Color</emphasis>
. Cranium, thorax, legs and abdomen castaneous; antenna testaceous; elytra bicolorous, mostly black, each elytron with three castaneous maculae, one in front of middle, one behind middle, and one at apex, only the apical macula reaches sutural margin. 
<emphasis box="[285,344,1430,1456]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="38">Head</emphasis>
. Cranium finely punctate, frons about as wide as length of antennal pedicel; EW/FW 70/20. 
<emphasis box="[1354,1432,1430,1456]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="38">Thorax</emphasis>
. Pronotum finely punctate, with 2 tumescences, concave at middle; PW/PL 155/190; elytra, asetiferous punctures substriate, punctures extend posteriorly slightly beyond elytral ½, width of interstitial spaces variable; EL/EW 590/110. 
<emphasis box="[294,400,1531,1557]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="38">Abdomen</emphasis>
. Female pygidium narrows slightly to a blunt point; female visible abdominal sternite VI with transverse flap (
<figureCitation box="[371,452,1565,1592]" captionStart="Figures 58–59" captionStartId="52.[192,279,647,673]" captionTargetBox="[192,1440,213,616]" captionTargetId="figure-11@52.[192,1440,213,616]" captionTargetPageId="52" captionText="Figures 58–59. Female genitalia. 58) Axina conspicua. 59) A. fortipes." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4564989" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4564989/files/figure.png" pageId="39" pageNumber="38">Fig. 59</figureCitation>
); aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[591,673,1565,1591]" captionStart="Figures 44–49" captionStartId="50.[192,279,1818,1844]" captionTargetBox="[320,1267,1056,1788]" captionTargetId="figure-38@50.[320,1267,1056,1788]" captionText="Figures 44–49. Aedeagi. 44) Axina chiasta. 45) A. conspicua. 46) A. fasciata. 47) A. centrimaculata. 48) A. fortipes. 49) A. furcula." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4586061" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4586061/files/figure.png" pageId="39" pageNumber="38">Fig. 48</figureCitation>
), phallobasic lobes very short, slightly diverged and curvate; phallic plates minutely serrate; phallobasic apodeme abbreviated.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="39.[192,1440,1640,1700]" pageId="39" pageNumber="38">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,310,1640,1666]" pageId="39" pageNumber="38">Variation.</emphasis>
Size. Length 10.0–14.0 mm; width 
<quantity box="[710,848,1641,1667]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.75" metricValueMax="3.3" metricValueMin="2.2" pageId="39" pageNumber="38" unit="mm" value="2.75" valueMax="3.3" valueMin="2.2">2.2–3.3 mm</quantity>
. In the 
<typeStatus box="[934,1032,1640,1666]" pageId="39" pageNumber="38">holotype</typeStatus>
specimen the premedial castaneous macula reached the sutural margin.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="39.[192,1075,1715,1742]" box="[192,1075,1715,1742]" pageId="39" pageNumber="38">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,376,1715,1742]" pageId="39" pageNumber="38">Natural history.</emphasis>
Specimens were collected in 
<collectingCountry box="[702,780,1716,1742]" name="Bolivia" pageId="39" pageNumber="38">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
during October, at 
<specimenCount box="[999,1075,1716,1742]" pageId="39" pageNumber="38" type="generic">
<quantity box="[999,1071,1716,1742]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.3" pageId="39" pageNumber="38" unit="m" value="430.0">430 m</quantity>
.
</specimenCount>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
